definitions.definition: A powerful angel that leads many other angels, but is still loyal to a deity , and often seen as belonging to a particular archangelical rank or order within a greater hierarchy of angels. ( Judeo-Christian examples: Gabriel , Michael , Raphael , Uriel ).
Synonym of angelica ( “ the garden herb ” ) .
